The paper focuses on developing a recommendation system based on multimodal data, which involves learning features from text, image, and video data. This aligns with the sub-categories of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Multimedia (cs.MM). The proposed model also involves deep learning techniques, which falls under the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and natural language processing (NLP), which are sub-fields of Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), respectively. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.CL.
